<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.4. ">Export Compliance Block</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>How to check:</strong> Account record &gt; Details section &gt; Compliance information &gt; "Export
        Compliance Block" checkbox.
    </li>
    <li>Export Compliance Block (ECB) is checked only at the Sold To CMF level.</li>
    <li>
        <strong>Case creation:</strong> if ECB is set, clicking "New R4C" displays an error and the case cannot be
        created. Hard stop.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Case edit:</strong> if ECB is set, clicking "Edit" displays an error and the case cannot be edited.
        Hard stop.
    </li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.5. ">Sold To Block Determination</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        From the Account record, open the related Business Account Group (BAG) record via 'Customer BAG Account
        Associations'.
    </li>
    <li>
        From the BAG record's Related tab, open 'Customer BAG CMF Associations' to see the related Customer CMF
        records.
    </li>
    <li>
        Open a Customer CMF record and check its related 'Customer Partners (Partner CMF)' records for role code.
    </li>
    <li>
        A Customer CMF record is a valid Sold To only if it has a related Customer Partner record with role code
        <strong>AG</strong>.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.5.1. ">Sold To CMF Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Three SAP blocks apply at CMF level: <strong>Central Order Block</strong>, <strong>Central Billing
            Block</strong>, <strong>Central Delivery Block</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
        If no CMF-level block is present, blocks are checked directly at Sales Area level instead (see below). CMF
        and Sales Area blocks are not both checked when CMF is already clear.
    </li>
    <li>Central Order Block = '01', '02', '03' or '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
    <li>Central Billing Block = '99' or '12' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
    <li>Central Delivery Block = '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Case creation: a Sold To CMF with any of the above blocks is excluded from the Sold To selection
                list entirely (it never becomes visible to select).
            </li>
            <li>
                Case edit: if any of the above blocks is present, clicking "Edit" shows an error toast and the case
                cannot be edited.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.5.2. ">Sold To Sales Area Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Based on the selected Sold To CMF, fetch the related Customer Sales Area records (CMF &gt; Related &gt;
        Customer Sales Area).
    </li>
    <li>
        The same three block types apply at Sales Area level: Order Block, Billing Block, Delivery Block, checked
        only when no CMF-level block was found.
    </li>
    <li>Order Block = '01', '02', '03' or '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
    <li>Billing Block = '99' or '12' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
    <li>Delivery Block = '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Case creation: a Sales Area with any of the above blocks is excluded from the Sales Area selection
                list.
            </li>
            <li>
                Case edit: if any of the above blocks is present, clicking "Edit" shows an error toast and the case
                cannot be edited.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">Payer Blocks</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        Based on the selected Sold To and Sales Area, the Payer is the related Customer Partner record with role
        code <strong>RG</strong>.
    </li>
    <li>
        If no Payer record is found, it is a hard stop and the Agent/Portal user is notified by an error toast.
    </li>
    <li>
        If at least one active Payer exists for the Sold To/Sales Area combination, its CMF and Sales Area records
        are checked for the blocks below.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.6.1. ">Payer CMF Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Central Order Block = '02' &rarr; hard stop, error message with block details.</li>
    <li>Central Billing Block = '08', '12' or '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.6.2. ">Payer Sales Area Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Order Block = '02' &rarr; hard stop, error message with block details.</li>
    <li>Billing Block = '08', '12' or '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Case creation: if any Payer-level block (CMF or Sales Area) is present, selecting the related Sold
                To triggers an error toast.
            </li>
            <li>
                Case edit: if any Payer-level block is present, clicking "Edit" shows an error toast and the case
                cannot be edited.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. ">Ship To Blocks</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        If no hard block exists at the Payer level, Ship To options are populated from Customer CMF records related
        to the selected Sold To/Sales Area with role code <strong>WE</strong>.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.7.1. ">Ship To CMF Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Order Block = '02' &rarr; hard stop, error message with block details.</li>
    <li>Delivery Block = '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-nh-numbering="1.7.2. ">Ship To Sales Area Blocks</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Order Block = '02' &rarr; hard stop, error message with block details.</li>
    <li>Delivery Block = '99' &rarr; hard stop, error toast with block details.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000007" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Case creation: a Ship To CMF/Sales Area with any of the above blocks is excluded from the Ship To
                selection list.
            </li>
            <li>
                Case edit: if any of the above blocks is present, clicking "Edit" shows an error toast and the case
                cannot be edited.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
